      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the dough, bulk ferment",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the first {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, {{nutmeg-ground}} and {{yeast-fast-action}} in a stand-mixer bowl. Add the lukewarm {{whole-milk}}, softened {{unsalted-butter}} and {{eggs}}. Mix on low for 7 minutes to a soft dough. Add the {{dried-currants}} and {{mixed-peel}}; mix briefly to incorporate. Bulk-ferment in an oiled bowl for 1 hour until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape, proof, pipe the cross",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Knock back and divide into 12 equal pieces (about 90 g each). Shape each into a tight ball and set on a lined tray, 3 cm apart, in a 4×3 grid. Proof for 90 minutes until puffed and the buns are touching. Heat the oven to 200°C fan. For the cross: whisk the second {{plain-flour}} with the first {{water}} to a smooth thick paste. Pipe a cross over each bun.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, glaze hot",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 18 to 20 minutes; the buns should be deep gold and the crosses should be set and pale. Dissolve the second {{caster-sugar}} in the second {{water}} in a small pan and bring to a simmer for 2 minutes. Brush the syrup generously over the hot buns as soon as they come out. Cool on a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
